begin_memory_text: Talked about where we were from - Chris is from Culver City, CA.  Talked about the weather in our areas.
middle_memory_text: Talked game shows in the area he lives in and that he attended a Price is Right filming.  Also, tried out for Jeopardy when he lived in Ohio.
end_memory_text: Talked about his tennis playing in high school and that I play pickleball.  Talked about buying expensive racquets at a thrift store for a cheap price.  Encouraged him to look up information on pickleball.
rest_of_day_open: My week will be busy with helping my daughter with her puppy.  I am going to play pickleball as much as the weather permits with the cold and rain.  I have some chores around the house to do.  I also have to help my aunt with shopping.  The weather maybe cold and rainy this week so I need to keep active with indoor activities.
critical_positive: Chris was fairly easy to talk to.  He seemed interested in sharing his stories about travelling with a band in which he played keyboard.  I felt I was the one who changed the topic a few times.  We both seemed relaxed and the conversation flowed smoothly and we both had something to add to each topic in our conversation.
critical_negative: I actually felt our conversation was very easy.  Chris was willing to share things about his life in the past.  Did not talk too much about his current situation.  Did not ask him about employment just because there is so much uncertainty in the workplace for so many and I didn't want him to feel uncomfortable.

begin_memory_text: In the beginning of the conversation, we discussed where we currently lived and I talked about living in Los Angeles, near Sony Pictures and from there we discussed game shows such as Jeopardy and Price is Right.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we talked about travels and locations and musicianship.  I mentioned playing in a band and having been to some locations where her daughter went to college. And she talked about her brother's forays into the musicians life.
end_memory_text: In the end we talked about sports.  Specifically tennis and pickleball.  I mentioned having played tennis earlier and she told me about pickleball and how she plays several times a week and hopes that they'll be indoor opportunities to play when the weather worsens for winter.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of the week is going.  I saw a mouse in the house and ordered a trap.  I see mice running around in the neighborhood so I hope it's not a nest, but I haven't been in a place with mice since I was a child.  Going to have to do some cleaning up and organizing and maybe call an exterminator if we can't figure it out.
critical_positive: We were both very polite and from the same general region of the country so conversation came very well and easy between us.  Each topic we brought up, we were both able to contribute do to similar experiences.  I played tennis, she played pickleball.  I was in a band, her brother was in a band.  My sister once lived where her daughter went to college.  Etc.
critical_negative: Everything worked pretty reasonably well.  Almost too reasonably for the time period we were allotted.  Since we both had things in common either directly or indirectly, we actually covered far fewer topics than we could have given the time constraints.  It's almost as if if we had less in common, we would have been able to learn more about each other.
